solution: ```class Solution {
public:
    int numberOfSubstrings(string s) {
        int n = s.size();
        int cnt[3] = {0, 0, 0};
        int left = 0, res = 0;
        for (int right = 0; right < n; ++right) {
            cnt[s[right] - 'a']++;
            while (cnt[0] && cnt[1] && cnt[2]) {
                res += n - right;
                cnt[s[left] - 'a']--;
                ++left;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Sliding-window counts occurrences of a, b, c. Once all three are present, every extension to the right forms a valid substring, so add n-right to the answer and shrink the left boundary to find the next window.

